      "<p class=\"c2 title\"><a name=\"h.azk7oos3s8cn\"></a><span>Vulnerability mentions in academic journals</span></p><p class=\"c7\"><span>The map shows the vulnerability indexes that co-occur in academic journals based on data from the Publish or Perish database. Indexes are linked to journals that they appear in by lines and clustered so that indexes that appear in the same journal are close to each other. </span></p><p class=\"c7 c9\"><span></span></p><p class=\"c7 c9\"><span></span></p><p class=\"c7 c24\"><span style=\"overflow: hidden; display: inline-block; margin: 0.00px 0.00px; border: 0.00px solid #000000; transform: rotate(0.00rad) translateZ(0px); -webkit-transform: rotate(0.00rad) translateZ(0px); width: 618.32px; height: 437.50px;\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/7OZA4e7k82_wq-gweAyoX_V7lpWACoVEf1moOgZsrlsw-i4nwP4GiY8QjG8qwaBuY3gm5xOWGx-opyELXfTHYbWKffz5zFBFNSbTVwQun80GqvrQorRQ6sh03A4\" style=\"width: 618.32px; height: 437.50px; margin-left: 0.00px; margin-top: 0.00px; transform: rotate(0.00rad) translateZ(0px); -webkit-transform: rotate(0.00rad) translateZ(0px);\" title=\"\"></span></p><h4 class=\"c2 c20\"><a name=\"h.sohw3tvzm6g8\"></a><span>Figure 1. Network of indexes occurring in journals in the Publish or Perish database. Indexes are linked to journals they appear in and arranged according to which indexes link to which journals. </span></h4><h1 class=\"c2 c22\"><a name=\"h.undpthsa1rf9\"></a><span>How to read the map</span></h1><p class=\"c7\"><span>The map shows a network of indexes and journals linkages. White circles represent journals and coloured circles represent the indexes. When two are linked together this means that an article in the journal cites the index it is linked to. Indexes and journals link together but journals do not link to other journals, or indexes to other indexes.</span></p><p class=\"c7 c9\"><span></span></p><p class=\"c7\"><span>The more connections a node has, the more times it has been cited in a journal, or cites an index. The human developement index is close to the centre of the network as it is cited by many different journals.</span></p><h1 class=\"c2 c22\"><a name=\"h.nfjvr2a5zplw\"></a><span>How the map is built (map building protocol)</span></h1><p class=\"c7 c27\"><span>18 indexes were selected with help from two experts </span><span class=\"c11\">S&ouml;nke Kreft (Germanwatch), Matthew</span><span>&nbsp;McKinnon (UNDP). </span><span class=\"c11\">The total list of indices can be found in Table 1 below. Not only did we include vulnerability indices, we also added economic models such as DICE and also other indices such as the Human Development Index (HDI). The reason that we added these indices is because these indices are also used in a climate adaptation context. Furthermore, these indices are used in competition with one another. The HDI is expected to be the most used index since it is one of the oldest indices and because it covers a broad field within climate change.</span></p><p class=\"c7 c9\"><span></span></p><a href=\"#\" name=\"43ff68a83f69a9b67adbb10c276b1776aeaf8c41\"></a><a href=\"#\" name=\"0\"></a><table cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"c28\"><tbody><tr class=\"c8\"><td class=\"c19\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c15\"><a class=\"c14\" href=\"https://www.google.com/url?q=https%3A%2F%2Fwiki.digitalmethods.net%2FDmi%2FEmapsAmsterdamSprint2014Project4UsesAndUsersOfVulnerabilityIndexes%3Fsortcol%3D0%3Btable%3D1%3Bup%3D0%23sorted_table&amp;sa=D&amp;sntz=1&amp;usg=AFQjCNGck4bGfd6tRyFUO1ppocuJ-8svzw\">Index Name</a></span></p></td><td class=\"c4\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c15\"><a class=\"c14\" href=\"https://www.google.com/url?q=https%3A%2F%2Fwiki.digitalmethods.net%2FDmi%2FEmapsAmsterdamSprint2014Project4UsesAndUsersOfVulnerabilityIndexes%3Fsortcol%3D1%3Btable%3D1%3Bup%3D0%23sorted_table&amp;sa=D&amp;sntz=1&amp;usg=AFQjCNH03Sqza8f-QC2lXtI5_3brnnvkiQ\">Abbreviation</a></span></p></td><td class=\"c17\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c15\"><a class=\"c14\" href=\"https://www.google.com/url?q=https%3A%2F%2Fwiki.digitalmethods.net%2FDmi%2FEmapsAmsterdamSprint2014Project4UsesAndUsersOfVulnerabilityIndexes%3Fsortcol%3D2%3Btable%3D1%3Bup%3D0%23sorted_table&amp;sa=D&amp;sntz=1&amp;usg=AFQjCNHazjI9BNPBzVubN5f1IUAGG0XNRA\">Type</a></span></p></td></tr><tr class=\"c8\"><td class=\"c23\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">Climate and Regional Economics of Development&rsquo;s vulnerability index</span></p></td><td class=\"c21\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">CRED</span></p></td><td class=\"c26\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">Vulnerability Index</span></p></td></tr><tr class=\"c8\"><td class=\"c3 c6\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c6 c12\"><a class=\"c14\" href=\"https://www.google.com/url?q=https%3A%2F%2Fwiki.digitalmethods.net%2Fbin%2Fedit%2FDmi%2FNatureServe%3Ftopicparent%3DDmi.EmapsAmsterdamSprint2014Project4UsesAndUsersOfVulnerabilityIndexes&amp;sa=D&amp;sntz=1&amp;usg=AFQjCNFh7k4Qh1YCtg6YJ82w7JT8XE3Fcw\">Nature Serve</a></span><span class=\"c6\">&nbsp;Climate Change Vulnerability Index</span></p></td><td class=\"c10 c6\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c6\">CCVI</span></p></td><td class=\"c5 c6\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c6\">Vulnerability Index</span></p></td></tr><tr class=\"c8\"><td class=\"c3\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">Environmental Vulnerability Index</span></p></td><td class=\"c10\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">EVI</span></p></td><td class=\"c5\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">Vulnerability Index</span></p></td></tr><tr class=\"c8\"><td class=\"c3 c6\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c6\">Climate Vulnerability Monitor</span></p></td><td class=\"c10 c6\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c6\">CVM</span></p></td><td class=\"c5 c6\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c6\">Vulnerability Index</span></p></td></tr><tr class=\"c8\"><td class=\"c3\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">Global Adaptation Index</span></p></td><td class=\"c10\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">GAIN</span></p></td><td class=\"c5\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">Vulnerability Index</span></p></td></tr><tr class=\"c8\"><td class=\"c3 c6\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c6\">Social Vulnerability Index</span></p></td><td class=\"c6 c10\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c6\">SVI</span></p></td><td class=\"c5 c6\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c6\">Vulnerability Index</span></p></td></tr><tr class=\"c8\"><td class=\"c3\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">Global Climate Risk Index</span></p></td><td class=\"c10\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">CRI</span></p></td><td class=\"c5\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">Vulnerability Index</span></p></td></tr><tr class=\"c8\"><td class=\"c3 c6\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c6\">Climate Change Performance Index</span></p></td><td class=\"c10 c6\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c6\">CCPI</span></p></td><td class=\"c5 c6\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c6\">Vulnerability Index</span></p></td></tr><tr class=\"c8\"><td class=\"c3\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">Dynamic Integrated Climate Change</span></p></td><td class=\"c10\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">DICE</span></p></td><td class=\"c5\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">Economic Model</span></p></td></tr><tr class=\"c8\"><td class=\"c3 c6\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c6\">Regional Integrated Climate and the Economy</span></p></td><td class=\"c10 c6\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c6\">RICE</span></p></td><td class=\"c5 c6\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c6\">Economic Model</span></p></td></tr><tr class=\"c8\"><td class=\"c3\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">Climate Framework for Uncertainty, Negotiation and Distribution</span></p></td><td class=\"c10\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">FUND</span></p></td><td class=\"c5\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">Economic Model</span></p></td></tr><tr class=\"c8\"><td class=\"c3 c6\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c6\">Model for Evaluating the Regional and Global Effects</span></p></td><td class=\"c10 c6\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c6\">MERGE</span></p></td><td class=\"c5 c6\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c6\">Economic Model</span></p></td></tr><tr class=\"c8\"><td class=\"c3\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">Human Development Index</span></p></td><td class=\"c10\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">HDI</span></p></td><td class=\"c5\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">Other</span></p></td></tr><tr class=\"c8\"><td class=\"c3 c6\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c6\">Multidimensional poverty index</span></p></td><td class=\"c10 c6\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c6\">MPI</span></p></td><td class=\"c5 c6\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c6\">Other</span></p></td></tr><tr class=\"c8\"><td class=\"c3\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">Human Poverty Index</span></p></td><td class=\"c10\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">HPI</span></p></td><td class=\"c5\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">Other</span></p></td></tr><tr class=\"c8\"><td class=\"c3 c6\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c6\">Gender-related Development Index</span></p></td><td class=\"c10 c6\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c6\">GDI</span></p></td><td class=\"c5 c6\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c6\">Other</span></p></td></tr><tr class=\"c8\"><td class=\"c3\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">Gender Inequality Index</span></p></td><td class=\"c10\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">GII</span></p></td><td class=\"c5\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">Other</span></p></td></tr><tr class=\"c8\"><td class=\"c6 c13\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c6\">Economic Vulnerability Index</span></p></td><td class=\"c6 c18\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c6\">ECVI</span></p></td><td class=\"c6 c16\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c6\">Other</span></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p class=\"c7 c9\"><span></span></p><p class=\"c7\"><span>The eighteen indexes were then queried in the Publish or Perish tool which searches Google scholar abstracts for key words. This produced a list of journals where indexes were mentioned. Gephi was then used to produce a network diagram. </span><span>Node position is determined by a force vector algorithm (Jacomy et al., forthcoming) bringing together terms directly or indirectly linked, and keeping away terms with fewer co-occurrences. Node size is proportional to their frequency in the corpus. Node color follows the clusters identified by the clustering algorithm. The names of the clusters have been attributed manually.</span></p><p class=\"c7 c9\"><span></span></p><p class=\"c7 c9\"><span></span></p><h1 class=\"c2 c22\"><a name=\"h.xo94nwvaky1k\"></a><span>References</span></h1><p class=\"c7\"><span>Jacomy et al., forthcoming<br></span></p><p class=\"c7 c9\"><span></span></p><p class=\"c7 c9\"><span></span></p><p class=\"c7 c9\"><span></span></p><p class=\"c7 c9\"><span></span></p><p class=\"c7 c9\"><span></span></p>"
